through the sale of Sogefi's stake in the German Boge group to Mannesmann.
In 1993 the group made an extraordinary gain of L12.3bn through the sale of
the SVAMA distribution subsidiary. Group net borrowings fell from L116.4bn
to L38.5bn.
The company said a strong presence in the second-hand car market and the
fact that its activities were centred both on Europe and the US enabled
sales to reach L660.4bn in 1993, against L664.5bn, despite recession in the
car industry.
