FT  23 MAR 94 / UK Company News: World of Leather in the red
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
World of Leather, the USM-quoted furniture retailer, ended 1993 with a
pre-tax deficit of Pounds 121,000, after taking account of a Pounds 406,000
exceptional charge representing the costs of a contractual dispute with its
former warehousing and distribution company.
The dispute was resolved in an out-of-court settlement just before the year
end, and involved a Pounds 150,000 payment by World of Leather.
The pre-tax outcome compared with Pounds 44,000 profits last time and came
from turnover up from Pounds 25.6m to Pounds 27.2m. Operating profits,
before exceptional items, increased from Pounds 526,000 to Pounds 588,000.
The improvement here, the company said, was achieved through improved
margins - up from 44.8 per cent to 47.1 per cent - which more than offset
higher distribution charges and administrative costs.
On December 26 the company opened its first new store for nearly four years,
increasing the number of outlets to 29.
Losses per share came out at 2.4p (0.1p earnings). The directors said that
provided there was no deterioration in the current level of trading it was
hoped the company would return to the dividend list this year. The last
payment was in 1989.
