FT  23 MAR 94 / Ferranti managers plan two buy-outs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN HAMILTON FAZEY, Northern Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Management teams running different parts of Ferranti International will this
week attempt two separate buy-outs from the receiver.
One team wants to buy Ferranti's components division in Oldham, Greater
Manchester. The other, based in Bracknell, Berkshire, wants to buy the
software division and enter a supply agreement for hardware from Oldham.
Arthur Andersen, the receiver, said yesterday there was outside interest in
buying the business whole, which might prove more convenient and attractive.
Andersen suggested potential buyers were not necessarily interested in
manufacturing and might subsequently divest from Oldham, where 450 people
are employed, possibly selling to the management.
The Oldham buy-out team, led by Mr Angus Mincher, managing director, has
made a bid after securing equity finance last week.
Mr Ian Sinderson of Ernst &amp; Young, the accountancy firm acting as the team's
corporate finance adviser, said three banks were competing to provide loan
and working capital.
The Bracknell buy-out team is being led by Mr Phil Burton, the local chief
executive. Finance is almost in place and the team expects to make a bid
this week.
The Ferranti group employs about 2,150 - a tenth of the payroll at its peak.
