FT  22 MAR 94 / International Company News: Credito Italiano turns in 36%
profits increase
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN SIMKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Credito Italiano, the newly privatised Italian bank which is the country's
seventh largest in terms of assets, yesterday reported a 36 per cent
increase in group net profits to L274.9bn (Dollars 164m) in 1993.
Interest income was up 16.8 per cent at L2,716.2bn while non-interest income
rose 75 per cent to L1,597bn.
The results, which follow a steep fall in net profits in 1992, reflect an
improved performance by subsidiaries. Gross operating profits were up 87 per
cent at L1,770.7bn.
